.5 [&amp;_>_*]:min-w-0"><h1 class=3D"text-2xl font-bold mt-1 text-text-200"=
 level=3D"1">Protected Routes in React</h1>
<p class=3D"whitespace-pre-wrap break-words">Protected routes are a fundame=
ntal concept in React applications that handle authentication and authoriza=
tion. They allow you to control access to certain parts of your application=
 based on user permissions or authentication status.</p>
<h2 class=3D"text-xl font-bold text-text-200 mt-1 -mb-0.5" level=3D"2">Core=
 Concept</h2>
<p class=3D"whitespace-pre-wrap break-words">At its heart, a protected rout=
e is a regular route with an added layer of conditional logic that determin=
es whether to:</p>
<ol class=3D"[&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:p=
b-1 list-decimal space-y-1.5 pl-7" depth=3D"0">
<li class=3D"whitespace-normal break-words" index=3D"0">Render the requeste=
d component (if the user is authorized)</li>
<li class=3D"whitespace-normal break-words" index=3D"1">Redirect the user e=
lsewhere, typically to a login page (if unauthorized)</li>
</ol>
