client side. For sensitive operations, always verify permissions on the ser=
ver too.</li>
<li class=3D"whitespace-normal break-words" index=3D"1"><strong>Flashing Co=
ntent</strong>: Without proper loading states, users might briefly see prot=
ected content before being redirected.</li>
<li class=3D"whitespace-normal break-words" index=3D"2"><strong>Authenticat=
ion Persistence</strong>: Consider how authentication persists across page =
refreshes (localStorage, cookies, etc.).</li>
<li class=3D"whitespace-normal break-words" index=3D"3"><strong>Deep Nested=
 Routes</strong>: Make sure protection applies correctly to nested routes.<=
/li>
</ol>
<p class=3D"whitespace-pre-wrap break-words">The approach you choose depend=
